        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "> When indexing a Dask array, it will return a 0-D array instead of a scalar. This differs from NumPy's behavior.\r\n\r\nThe only way we could sensibly change this would be to introduce a scalar type for dask array, but I don't think that's a good idea. The distinction between 0-d arrays and scalars is confusing enough in NumPy.",
